heisigStory: As with four, we shall postpone learning the primitive elements that make up this character. Note how the general principle we just learned in the preceding frame applies to the writing of the character for five.
koohiiStory2: This Kanji looks like a "3" Kanji with two added vertical lines. 3+2= 5.
readingExamples: 五 (いつ), 五つ (いつ.つ)
words: five days, the fifth day (of the month)
